obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32541)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title.`
  content `This Act may be called the Reserve Bank (Transfer to Public Ownership) Act, 1948.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244&sectionId=32541&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32542)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244&sectionId=32542&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means such day as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint;`
  line
  line `(b) "Bank" means the Reserve Bank of India as constituted by the principal Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) "principal Act" means the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32543)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer of Bank shares`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244&sectionId=32543&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the appointed day--`
  line
  line `(a) all shares in the capital of the Bank shall by virtue of this Act be deemed to be transferred free`
  line `of all trusts, liabilities and encumbrances to the Central Government, and`
  line
  line `(b) as full compensation there for, the Central Government shall issue to every person who,`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, is registered as the holder of any such shares, an amount`
  line `calculated at the rate of one hundred and eighteen rupees and ten annas per share, in promissory notes`
  line `of the Central Government bearing interest at the rate of three per centum per annum repayable at par`
  line `on such date as may be specified in this behalf by the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the amount so calculated is not an exact multiple of one hundred rupees the`
  line `amount in excess of the nearest lower multiple of one hundred rupees shall be paid by cheque drawn`
  line `on the Bank:`
  line
  line `Provided further hat in respect of any share obtained at par from the Central Government by any`
  line `Director of the Bank in pursuance of sub-section (8) of section 4 of the principal Act as in force`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, the said amount shall be calculated at the rate of one hundred`
  line `rupees per share.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding the transfer of shares effected by this section any shareholder who, immediately`
  line `before the appointed day, is entitled to payment of dividend on the shares held by him shall be entitled to`
  line `receive from the Bank--`
  line
  line `(a) all dividends accruing due on his shares in respect of the year ending on the 30th day of June,`
  line `1948, or any preceding year remaining unpaid on the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(b) dividends calculated at the rate of four rupees per annum per share in respect of the period`
  line `from the 1st day of July, 1948, to the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (42819)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Vacation of office by existing office bearers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244&sectionId=42819&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On the appointed day any person who`
  line `immediately before that day was holding office as a Director of the Central Board otherwise than as`
  line `Governor or Deputy Governor or as a member of a Local Board of the Bank shall vacate his office, and`
  line `the Central Board and the Local Boards of the Bank shall thereafter be constituted in the manner`
  line `prescribed by sections 8 and 9 of the principal Act as amended by this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32544)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Interim arrangements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244&sectionId=32544&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Pending the constitution of the Central Board under section 8 of the`
  line `principal Act as amended by this Act, the Governor of the Bank, or in his absence a Deputy Governor of`
  line `the Bank duly nominated by him in this behalf, may, subject to such restrictions and conditions as may`
  line `from time to time be imposed by the Central Government, exercise all powers, and do all acts and things`
  line `which may be exercised or done by the Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32545)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Rule-making power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1 Added by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244&sectionId=32545&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for the purpose of giving effect to the objects of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line provide--
  line
  line `(a) for the manner in which and the authority by which compensation shall be paid under section`
  line `3; and`
  line
  line `(b) for the determination of persons to whom compensation is so payable.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32546)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244&sectionId=32546&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00027_194862_1517807322244
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment to Act 2 of 1934.]--Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1950 (35 of 1950), s. 2`
  line `and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 10-4-1950).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
